{"lemma":"والِدٌ","slug":"والِدٌ","root":"#.ل.د","root_slug":"_-ل-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ل-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"والِد","root":"ولد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":14},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42360"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"father"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"parent","examples":[{"text":"وَالِدَانِ","english":"(two) parents"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"paternal relatives","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of وَلَدَ (walada, “to give birth”)."},"ipa":["/waː.lid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42360","headword_ar":"وَالِدٌ","root":"wld","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidapN","text_ar":"وَالِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, K) the former as a possessive epithet, and the latter as an act. part. n. (M, L.) A woman, and any pregnant animal,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a child"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bringing forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, M, L.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidN","text_ar":"وَالِدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidapN","text_ar":"وَالِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, Msb;) [which latter is the more common in this sense:] pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAliduwna","text_ar":"وَالِدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and of the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidaAtN","text_ar":"وَالِدَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidaAni","text_ar":"وَالِدَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two parents;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"father and mother."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN waAlidN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ وَالِدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pregnant ewe"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, A, L, Msb, K; *) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidapN","text_ar":"وَالِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waluwdN","text_ar":"وَلُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wulodN","text_ar":"وُلْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in the L, and most other lexicons, accord. to the TA, and in some copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wul~adN","text_ar":"وُلَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in the A, and in other copies of the K,) each of which is correct. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prolific ewe"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat; that breeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brings forth, plentifully;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, L;) [as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waluwdN","text_ar":"وَلُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": see S, K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^bd","text_ar":"ابد"},{"kind":"text","text":": see also an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waluwdN","text_ar":"وَلُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaA^u","text_ar":"اَسْوَاُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino $ar~i","text_ar":"مِنْ شَرِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlidK wamaA walada","text_ar":"وَالِدٍ وَمَا وَلَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad. respecting prayer for God's protection, [lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From the evil of a parent and what he hath begotten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said to mean Iblees and the devils: (L:) or Adam and the true friends and the prophets and the martyrs and the believers whom he hath begotten. (El-Basáïr.)"}],"source_refs":["M","L","K","S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}